        <title>Gamemode</title>
        <link>https://saipheblue.github.io/p/gamemode/</link>
        <pubDate>Mon, 03 Feb 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://saipheblue.github.io/p/gamemode/</guid>
        <description>&lt;img src="https://saipheblue.github.io/p/gamemode/1.png" alt="Featured image of post Gamemode" /&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-is-gamemode&#34;&gt;What is gamemode?
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The command &lt;code&gt;gamemoderun %command%&lt;/code&gt; is used on Linux to run a game or application with Gamemode, a tool designed to optimize your system for gaming. It tweaks settings like the CPU governor, I/O priority, and more to give your games a performance boost.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;how-it-works&#34;&gt;How It Works
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;gamemoderun&lt;/code&gt;: This is the command that activates Gamemode.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;%command%&lt;/code&gt;: This is a placeholder for the actual command used to launch your game or app. It’s commonly used in Steam’s launch options.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re running a game through Steam, you might add the following to the game’s launch options:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;gamemoderun %command%&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This ensures the game runs with Gamemode optimizations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://saipheblue.github.io/p/gamemode/2.png&#34;
	width=&#34;523&#34;
	height=&#34;133&#34;
	srcset=&#34;https://saipheblue.github.io/p/gamemode/2_hu_1470256ba24ccd4d.png 480w, https://saipheblue.github.io/p/gamemode/2_hu_572189de217f4edf.png 1024w&#34;
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
	
		class=&#34;gallery-image&#34; 
		data-flex-grow=&#34;393&#34;
		data-flex-basis=&#34;943px&#34;
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;installation&#34;&gt;Installation
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you don’t have Gamemode installed, you can install it on Arch Linux using:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo pacman -S gamemode
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;To check if Gamemode is active, run:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;gamemoded -s
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;This will show whether Gamemode is running.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-does-gamemode-optimize&#34;&gt;What Does Gamemode Optimize?
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Gamemode can tweak a variety of settings to improve gaming performance, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CPU Governor:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Locks your CPU at top speed for better performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I/O Priority:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gives your game priority access to your disk, reducing stuttering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Process Niceness:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Makes sure your game gets more attention from the CPU.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kernel Scheduler:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adjusts how tasks are handled to keep your game running smoothly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Screensaver Inhibiting:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stops your screensaver from interrupting your game.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GPU Performance Mode:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimizes your GPU for gaming (supports NVIDIA and AMD, plus overclocking for NVIDIA).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CPU Core Management:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pins or parks CPU cores to improve performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Custom Scripts:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lets you add your own tweaks for even more control.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;availability&#34;&gt;Availability
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Gamemode packages are available for Ubuntu, Debian, Solus, Arch, Gentoo, Fedora, OpenSUSE, Mageia and possibly more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;is-it-worth-it&#34;&gt;Is It Worth It?
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;While not all games will see a huge improvement, Gamemode is a simple and effective way to squeeze out extra performance. If you’re a Linux gamer, it’s definitely worth a try!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more details, check out the &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://github.com/FeralInteractive/gamemode&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;Github repository&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
        </item>
        <item>
        <title>Quick Tools to Manage Space Usage</title>
        <link>https://saipheblue.github.io/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/</link>
        <pubDate>Tue, 21 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://saipheblue.github.io/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/</guid>
        <description>&lt;img src="https://saipheblue.github.io/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/1.png" alt="Featured image of post Quick Tools to Manage Space Usage" /&gt;&lt;p&gt;From time to time, you might need to free up disk space, but where do you start? How can you quickly locate those large files taking up valuable storage? Let’s explore some options. Spoiler alert: The first two are my top picks!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;terminal&#34;&gt;Terminal
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Command to Locate Large Files&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;find / -type f -size +2000M 2&amp;gt;/dev/null
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;/&lt;/code&gt;: Search from the root directory (change to specific directories like /home or /var for faster results).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;-type f&lt;/code&gt;: Search for files only.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;-size +2000M&lt;/code&gt;: Files larger than 2000 MB.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;2&amp;gt;/dev/null&lt;/code&gt;: Suppress permission denied errors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://saipheblue.github.io/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/2.png&#34;
	width=&#34;917&#34;
	height=&#34;91&#34;
	srcset=&#34;https://saipheblue.github.io/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/2_hu_265e8a25a28c8d98.png 480w, https://saipheblue.github.io/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/2_hu_8b5ab8f484028146.png 1024w&#34;
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;find / -type f&#34;
	
	
		class=&#34;gallery-image&#34; 
		data-flex-grow=&#34;1007&#34;
		data-flex-basis=&#34;2418px&#34;
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;ncdu&#34;&gt;Ncdu
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Install ncdu:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo pacman -S ncdu
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Run ncdu:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;ncdu /
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Use arrow keys to navigate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://saipheblue.github.io/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/1.png&#34;
	width=&#34;850&#34;
	height=&#34;428&#34;
	srcset=&#34;https://saipheblue.github.io/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/1_hu_cc3afc7aff852d76.png 480w, https://saipheblue.github.io/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/1_hu_78d099765d46c35c.png 1024w&#34;
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;ncdu&#34;
	
	
		class=&#34;gallery-image&#34; 
		data-flex-grow=&#34;198&#34;
		data-flex-basis=&#34;476px&#34;
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;gui-tool&#34;&gt;GUI tool
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you prefer graphical tools, you can use baobab:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo pacman -S baobab
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://saipheblue.github.io/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/3.png&#34;
	width=&#34;958&#34;
	height=&#34;597&#34;
	srcset=&#34;https://saipheblue.github.io/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/3_hu_af4e6bae8dc9cf82.png 480w, https://saipheblue.github.io/p/quick-tools-to-manage-space-usage/3_hu_97fdc23f77cee819.png 1024w&#34;
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;baobab&#34;
	
	
		class=&#34;gallery-image&#34; 
		data-flex-grow=&#34;160&#34;
		data-flex-basis=&#34;385px&#34;
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;package-cache&#34;&gt;Package cache
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Check cache size:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-gdscript3&#34; data-lang=&#34;gdscript3&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;du&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;sh&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;var&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;cache&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;pacman&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;pkg&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Clean package cache:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo pacman -Sc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;To remove all cached packages:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo pacman -Scc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;log-files&#34;&gt;Log files
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Check log sizes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-gdscript3&#34; data-lang=&#34;gdscript3&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;sudo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;du&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;sh&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;var&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;log&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;/*&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Clear logs ( use with caution !!! ):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-gdscript3&#34; data-lang=&#34;gdscript3&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;sudo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;truncate&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;s&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;var&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;log&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;filename&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;log&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</description>
